  "texts": [
    "Those percentages remained consistent across types of VR experiences with varying DoF.The following conclusions were drawn on the basis of the above data.",
    "Generally, more complex experiences make greater use of characters, audio, and interface.",
    "A conclusion that is not surprising, as higher complexity in the iVR experience requires more elements for interaction and feedback.",
    "An exception to that trend was observed in Passive experiences, where the use of characters (exclusively Recorded) and audio was higher.",
    "It may be attributed to the non-interactive nature of Passive experiences, as both audio and Recorded characters were pre-recorded resources."
  ],
